5. Implement the following Invoice Item class in Java according to the given
UML class diagram:

SOURCE CODE:[InvoiceItem.java]

package Basics;
public class InvoiceItem {
    // Fields (attributes)
    private String id;
    private String desc;
    private int qty;
    private double unitPrice;

    // Constructor
    public InvoiceItem(String id, String desc, int qty, double unitPrice) {
        this.id = id;
        this.desc = desc;
        this.qty = qty;
        this.unitPrice = unitPrice;
    }

    public String getID() {
        return id;
    }

    public String getDesc() {
        return desc;
    }

    public int getQty() {
        return qty;
    }

    public double getUnitPrice() {
        return unitPrice;
    }

    public void setQty(int qty) {
        this.qty = qty;
    }

    public void setUnitPrice(double unitPrice) {
        this.unitPrice = unitPrice;
    }

    public double getTotal() {
        return unitPrice * qty;
    }

    // toString method
    public String toString() {
        return "InvoiceItem[id=" + id + ",desc=" + desc + ",qty=" + qty + ",unitPrice=" + unitPrice + "]";
    }
}


//To access it Declare another class

SOURECE CODE:[InvoiveMain]

Public class InvoiveMain(String[] args){
 public static void main(String[] args) {
        InvoiceItem item = new InvoiceItem("A001", "Java Book", 3, 345.0);
  System.out.println(item.getID());           // A001
        System.out.println(item.getDesc());         // Java Book
        System.out.println(item.getQty());          // 3
        System.out.println(item.getUnitPrice());    // 345.0
        System.out.println(item.getTotal());        
        System.out.println(item);                   
    }
}

OUTPUT:

A001
Java Book
3
345.0
1035.0
InvoiceItem[id=A001,desc=Java Book,qty=3,unitPrice=345.0]
